Jordan First-Half Budget Deficit Widens to 259.9 Million Dinars

-- B y   M o h a m m a d   T a y s e e r
-- 
2011-08-08T11:48:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/jordan-first-half-budget-deficit-widens-to-259-9-million-dinars.html
Jordanâ€™s budget deficit widened to
259.9 million dinars ($367 million) in the first half of 2011
from 167.2 million dinars a year earlier, the  Finance Ministry 
said.  Grants rose to 315.1 million dinars by the end of June, up
from 157.8 million dinars a year earlier, the Amman-based
ministry said in a statement posted on its  website .  Total expenditures rose to 2.8 billion dinars in the first
six months of the year from 2.6 billion dinars during the same
period last year, the statement said.  Domestic revenue slipped to 2.24 billion dinars during the
first six months of this year compared to 2.26 billion dinars a
year earlier, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
